snippet: Since President Zine el-Abidine Ben Ali was ousted in January 2011, the unemployment rate in Tunisia has risen to 18 percent from 13 percent, meaning some 750,000 people are out of work.
abstract: Frustration among Tunisians that people are not better off is starting to overflow again, two years after the riots that began over economic frustration and unemployment toppled government and started Arab Spring.
lead_paragraph: Since President Zine el-Abidine Ben Ali was ousted in January 2011, the unemployment rate in Tunisia has risen to 18 percent from 13 percent, meaning some 750,000 people are out of work.
